      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "KARINYA SHALL BE (1) was quickly into stride and burnt early from the middle draw where she gave a sight, finishing third (18.75) and beaten 5 lengths over 318m at Dubbo. Sure to be about the mark. EVA CARGO (2) hit the ground running from the squeeze draw with a fast early split last time, but run over late and missed the frame when a 1.5 lengths fourth (19.86) over 340m at this track. Strong form has emerged from her last run. One of the main contenders. HARA'S ROCKY (5) was strongly fancied latest and proved too good with a half a length win at this track in a handy 20.32. Has a tricky draw to overcome but has a good record over this journey. Deserves serious consideration again. IRINKA CLAY (3) has ability and can feature with the right run after missing a cheque here most recently.",
